WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.040 --> 00:00:08.040
[thunder rumbling]

2
00:00:09.400 --> 00:00:10.800
[carabiner clinks]

3
00:00:14.120 --> 00:00:15.560
[exhales]

4
00:00:17.480 --> 00:00:19.880
[tense music playing]

5
00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:28.120
[instructor] Stop there!

6
00:00:29.560 --> 00:00:30.400
Unhook yourself.

7
00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:32.960
Go on!

8
00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:40.120
Stop! Hold it.

9
00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:43.280
If I told you to jump off a cliff.
would you do it?

10
00:00:44.080 --> 00:00:46.720
We want soldiers
who can think for themselves. not sheep!

11
00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:48.440
That's it. you're done.

12
00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:51.960
[instructor over comm]
<i>Send the next one up.</i>

13
00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:53.040
[officer] Villiers!

14
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:56.160
Next up. Villiers!

15
00:00:58.880 --> 00:01:01.560
[tense music continues]

16
00:01:05.400 --> 00:01:06.600
[woman exhales]

17
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:14.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

18
00:01:21.640 --> 00:01:22.560
[Villiers exhales]

19
00:01:26.320 --> 00:01:27.720
[instructor] Step out. let's go!

20
00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:29.960
Go on!

21
00:01:40.680 --> 00:01:42.640
[thunder crashes]

22
00:01:45.120 --> 00:01:46.360
Stop!

23
00:01:46.440 --> 00:01:47.480
Look at me. Look at me!

24
00:01:51.200 --> 00:01:52.800
Lift your arms up.

25
00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:02.640
Unhook yourself.

26
00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:05.040
No!

27
00:02:05.120 --> 00:02:07.480
What did you say?
What's the matter. you scared?

28
00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:10.560
I'm not scared. sir.
I just don't take unnecessary risks!

29
00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:14.400
Fine. head to the end then.

30
00:02:17.280 --> 00:02:19.280
[tense music continues]

31
00:02:24.520 --> 00:02:26.760
[instructor] Stop! Lift your right knee.

32
00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:31.000
[exhales]

33
00:02:31.720 --> 00:02:32.600
Now. sing!

34
00:02:35.560 --> 00:02:36.560
I said. sing!

35
00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:43.960
[sings in French]

36
00:02:44.600 --> 00:02:46.800
[in English] I can't hear you!
You hear anything?

37
00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:49.080
[Villiers continues singing in French]

38
00:03:02.200 --> 00:03:04.320
[in English] Alright.
that's enough! Can it!

39
00:03:04.400 --> 00:03:06.640
What's with the oldies?
Don't tell me you like Piaf?

40
00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:09.040
Just one of those hopeless romantics. sir!

41
00:03:09.120 --> 00:03:10.960
Alright. come on back!

42
00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:13.000
- Hold on!
- [tense music continues]

43
00:03:22.320 --> 00:03:23.400
Why are you here?

44
00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:25.680
I want to be a part of the GIGN. sir!

45
00:03:25.760 --> 00:03:26.760
Yeah. why?

46
00:03:26.840 --> 00:03:29.200
It's the best in the world!
The best counter-terrorism--

47
00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:31.480
Yeah. yeah.
I've seen the recruitment ads too.

48
00:03:31.560 --> 00:03:33.200
Why are you here. Max?

49
00:03:36.200 --> 00:03:37.800
Because I can be the best. sir!

50
00:03:37.880 --> 00:03:39.360
Better than your dad?

51
00:03:41.560 --> 00:03:44.200
You got what it takes. Max? Can you do it?

52
00:03:47.680 --> 00:03:49.600
Honestly. I don't know yet.

53
00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:54.440
But it's the only thing I want to do.
and I'll give anything to prove it.

54
00:03:59.960 --> 00:04:01.480
[instructor] Next. Lemoine!

55
00:04:04.640 --> 00:04:06.400
Why'd they ask you all that stuff?

56
00:04:07.680 --> 00:04:09.840
It's nothing.
just bullshit to throw us off.

57
00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:12.680
[music fades]

58
00:04:12.760 --> 00:04:14.360
Good thing you pushed the kid.

59
00:04:15.280 --> 00:04:18.240
You don't want people saying
you're playing favorites with your godson.

60
00:04:19.640 --> 00:04:20.880
You did the right thing.

61
00:04:26.280 --> 00:04:30.000
ELITE FORCE

62
00:04:35.480 --> 00:04:38.240
[coach] Come on. guys!
Pick it up! Let's go!

63
00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:39.960
- Come on!
- [grunting]

64
00:04:40.040 --> 00:04:42.040
[exhales sharply]

65
00:04:43.440 --> 00:04:46.200
[officer] Trainees.
as soon as you're ready. start the count.

66
00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:50.000
- [trainee 1] Shooter one. ready.
- [trainee 2] Shooter two. ready.

67
00:04:50.720 --> 00:04:52.840
{\an8}AN AUDACIOUS MOVE

68
00:04:52.920 --> 00:04:56.920
[auspicious music playing]

69
00:04:59.360 --> 00:05:02.520
[officer] Three. two. one.

70
00:05:06.720 --> 00:05:08.480
{\an8}KOUACHI
THE FINAL ASSAULT

71
00:05:12.560 --> 00:05:14.440
- [both exhale]
- [coach] Let's go! 13!

72
00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:16.280
Fourteen!

73
00:05:17.360 --> 00:05:18.200
Fifteen!

74
00:05:18.280 --> 00:05:19.920
CAUTION
ELECTRIC FENCE

75
00:05:28.560 --> 00:05:30.800
[man on radio] <i>Overcast day</i>
<i>lined up for us today.</i>

76
00:05:30.880 --> 00:05:33.320
<i>but no need to bring those umbrellas.</i>
<i>we're not expecting rain.</i>

77
00:05:34.120 --> 00:05:35.280
[woman] <i>Where are you?</i>

78
00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:37.640
Coming. yeah. I'm here.

79
00:05:39.800 --> 00:05:41.480
That's pretty nice.

80
00:05:41.560 --> 00:05:42.920
<i>- Is it new?</i>
- What. this?

81
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:44.560
{\an8}<i>- Yeah.</i>
- [chuckles]

82
00:05:44.640 --> 00:05:46.200
{\an8}<i>Yeah. You like it?</i>

83
00:05:46.280 --> 00:05:47.320
Yeah. I do.

84
00:05:48.840 --> 00:05:51.160
- Do you have the matching set?
- [chuckles]

85
00:05:51.240 --> 00:05:52.080
You guess.

86
00:05:52.680 --> 00:05:55.400
- Show me.
- No. I don't think I will.

87
00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:56.760
<i>- Come on.</i>
- No.

88
00:05:56.840 --> 00:06:00.160
<i>I'll show you as soon as you hand in</i>
<i>your resignation and come back to Paris.</i>

89
00:06:00.240 --> 00:06:02.520
<i>You know I have to wait</i>
<i>until the recruitment's over.</i>

90
00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:04.600
Hello. sweetheart!

91
00:06:06.120 --> 00:06:09.040
<i>- You're just gonna take it without asking?</i>
<i>- If I asked. you'd just say no!</i>

92
00:06:09.120 --> 00:06:10.560
Hello. pretty girl!

93
00:06:10.640 --> 00:06:13.400
Never mind. she's gone.
16-year-olds are like that!

94
00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:16.240
- Doesn't even say hi to her dad?
- [sighs]

95
00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:19.000
<i>That's okay. I'll see her tonight</i>
<i>at the academy anyway.</i>

96
00:06:20.840 --> 00:06:21.960
That was yesterday.

97
00:06:22.720 --> 00:06:24.640
- You're joking.
- I'm not.

98
00:06:24.720 --> 00:06:26.960
<i>Her rehearsal was always on the 5th.</i>

99
00:06:27.040 --> 00:06:28.200
Ah. fuck…

100
00:06:29.760 --> 00:06:31.520
I really thought it was tonight.

101
00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.200
- How was it?
- [pager beeping]

102
00:06:34.280 --> 00:06:36.280
ALERT 1

103
00:06:36.880 --> 00:06:37.760
Call you back later.

104
00:06:37.840 --> 00:06:38.880
<i>I have to go.</i>

105
00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:42.480
[suspenseful music playing]

106
00:06:42.560 --> 00:06:44.160
[alarm blaring]

107
00:06:44.240 --> 00:06:45.400
Let's go. come on!

108
00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:49.320
Move. Let's move! Through here.

109
00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:51.880
[man] The army's weapons depot
in Châteaudun.

110
00:06:51.960 --> 00:06:54.040
Four soldiers were shot dead. unprovoked.

111
00:06:54.120 --> 00:06:55.640
I can see that.

112
00:06:55.720 --> 00:06:58.400
[man] Two other soldiers are missing.
They could be hostages.

113
00:06:58.480 --> 00:07:00.640
It was quick. brutal. efficient.

114
00:07:00.720 --> 00:07:03.560
AK-47. AK-47. and an Uzi?

115
00:07:03.640 --> 00:07:05.040
An Uzi. yeah.

116
00:07:05.120 --> 00:07:07.800
[woman] The terrorists
obviously knew the area well.

117
00:07:07.880 --> 00:07:10.440
They knew where the cameras were
and shot a few out.

118
00:07:10.520 --> 00:07:14.440
It was intentional. precise. cold.
They're pros.

119
00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:16.680
We're still looking
for anything to ID them.

120
00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:18.640
Seems like they're used
to working together.

121
00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:19.960
Maybe they're mercenaries.

122
00:07:20.040 --> 00:07:22.480
But why take such a big risk
for some firearms?

123
00:07:22.560 --> 00:07:23.960
You can get guns anywhere.

124
00:07:24.040 --> 00:07:27.400
Well. this is an unusual case.
The pallets are loaded with explosives.

125
00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:29.840
CL-20. An experimental compound.

126
00:07:29.920 --> 00:07:32.480
- So that's what they took. huh?
- [man] Just as it came in.

127
00:07:32.560 --> 00:07:35.960
Most powerful explosive currently known.
And there was a ton.

128
00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:39.000
Do we have a location for these guys?

129
00:07:39.080 --> 00:07:41.600
Not yet. I've got Recon
going over everything right now.

130
00:07:41.680 --> 00:07:43.800
They just got the pictures.
They'll find 'em.

131
00:07:43.880 --> 00:07:47.800
I've taken Tanya off Demo. She's with you.
Stop this truck and retrieve the cargo.

132
00:07:47.880 --> 00:07:49.520
I'm leaving you
in charge of the operation.

133
00:07:49.600 --> 00:07:52.280
- You're not coming with us?
- I'm not the one the guys need out there.

134
00:07:52.360 --> 00:07:53.840
I'll stay at Command.

135
00:07:53.920 --> 00:07:56.800
- Wait. we've got a clear cam here.
- Pull it up for us.

136
00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:00.760
[woman] Right there. on the roof.

137
00:08:00.840 --> 00:08:03.720
- That's a cooling unit.
- Right. Which means it has a GPS chip.

138
00:08:04.320 --> 00:08:06.840
We'll check with the police
and trace the truck that way.

139
00:08:07.920 --> 00:08:09.800
We'll keep your unit on the ground.
in support.

140
00:08:09.880 --> 00:08:11.320
- You'll man the gun.
- Okay.

141
00:08:11.400 --> 00:08:13.880
We have a chopper in
from Villacoublay just now.

142
00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:15.600
- And we'll take the 82.
- Alright.

143
00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:18.680
Chloé. can you keep us
posted on the truck? Let's move.

144
00:08:18.760 --> 00:08:19.960
[Chloé] Yeah.

145
00:08:20.040 --> 00:08:22.840
[pensive music playing]

146
00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:27.680
COMMIT FOR LIFE

147
00:08:34.560 --> 00:08:36.680
[music turns dramatic]

148
00:08:36.760 --> 00:08:39.040
- [pilot 1] Circuit breakers on?
- [pilot 2] Breakers on.

149
00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:40.440
[pilot 1] I've got the radios.

150
00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:42.520
[helicopter engine whirring]

151
00:08:46.800 --> 00:08:49.280
[dramatic music continues]

152
00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:53.040
[gun cocks]

153
00:09:03.160 --> 00:09:05.240
[pilot 1] Re-centered.
Pre-flight complete.

154
00:09:05.320 --> 00:09:06.640
[pilot 2] Copy.

155
00:09:08.440 --> 00:09:09.880
[Cédric] Alright. let's go!

156
00:09:16.120 --> 00:09:17.600
[man] Take vehicle 4. alright?

157
00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:20.640
[Cédric] Here comes the reinforcements.
Glad you're here. Demo!

158
00:09:20.720 --> 00:09:22.320
- [Tanya] You good?
- Yeah.

159
00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:24.240
Priority to the departing team.

160
00:09:24.320 --> 00:09:27.400
Hey. Mustachio. show your elders
some respect and get inside. would ya?

161
00:09:27.480 --> 00:09:29.880
Yeah. and try not to forget
I can blow your balls off too.

162
00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:32.120
Might have trouble blowing up
something that small!

163
00:09:32.200 --> 00:09:34.800
- [chuckles]
- [chuckles] C'mon. get in with me.

164
00:09:34.880 --> 00:09:36.040
Slick ride you got.

165
00:09:36.120 --> 00:09:38.680
Yeah. got her last week.
Seized from a race at the Spanish border.

166
00:09:39.560 --> 00:09:42.040
[engines rumble]

167
00:09:42.120 --> 00:09:43.760
[door slams]

168
00:09:43.840 --> 00:09:46.200
[dramatic music continues]

169
00:09:47.160 --> 00:09:48.480
[woman] They're heading out!

170
00:09:50.640 --> 00:09:52.400
We're not finishing up first?

171
00:09:52.480 --> 00:09:54.800
Mop all you want. man.
We're watching the action.

172
00:10:02.800 --> 00:10:03.640
Let's go.

173
00:10:04.480 --> 00:10:06.480
[indistinct chatter]

174
00:10:07.960 --> 00:10:09.760
- Sit down. It's fine.
- [Christophe] General.

175
00:10:14.200 --> 00:10:16.200
[engines revving]

176
00:10:17.800 --> 00:10:18.840
We're taking off. let's go!

177
00:10:18.920 --> 00:10:21.680
[Chloé on comm] <i>We've got 'em.</i>
<i>His GPS puts him 40 kilometers away.</i>

178
00:10:21.760 --> 00:10:24.040
<i>on a back road heading towards Chartres.</i>

179
00:10:24.120 --> 00:10:26.600
[Cédric] <i>Okay.</i>
<i>we're all converging on the A10.</i>

180
00:10:26.680 --> 00:10:29.080
[Christophe] There are
reportedly two hostages.

181
00:10:30.040 --> 00:10:32.320
What're you doing out there? Hello!

182
00:10:34.240 --> 00:10:35.760
Villiers. Colonel.

183
00:10:35.840 --> 00:10:38.520
We heard the team was heading out.
We wanted to show our support.

184
00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:42.480
Get the fuck over there.
I don't wanna hear you.

185
00:10:42.560 --> 00:10:43.840
You're invisible. Got it?

186
00:10:47.960 --> 00:10:49.960
[intense music playing]

187
00:12:05.120 --> 00:12:06.640
[David] We've got eyes on the truck.

188
00:12:07.480 --> 00:12:09.200
[music turns suspenseful]

189
00:12:13.040 --> 00:12:14.960
<i>It's at kilometer 81. heading south.</i>

190
00:12:16.040 --> 00:12:17.960
<i>It's just the truck. no other vehicles.</i>

191
00:12:18.040 --> 00:12:19.880
<i>He's moving fast.</i>

192
00:12:21.920 --> 00:12:23.920
[suspenseful music continues]

193
00:12:33.120 --> 00:12:35.520
There's a town coming up ahead.
1.5 clicks out.

194
00:12:35.600 --> 00:12:38.600
[Chloé] There's also a school
at the edge of the urban area.

195
00:12:38.680 --> 00:12:40.160
JULES FERRY ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

196
00:12:41.120 --> 00:12:42.040
That could be a target.

197
00:12:43.320 --> 00:12:44.960
[Tanya] They're carrying a ton of CL-20.

198
00:12:45.800 --> 00:12:48.120
If it goes up.
it'll wipe out the whole neighborhood.

199
00:12:48.200 --> 00:12:51.720
- That won't happen.
- It might explode and take you down.

200
00:12:51.800 --> 00:12:54.320
[David] If you've got a better idea.
I'm all ears.

201
00:12:54.880 --> 00:12:57.120
Otherwise. you know what we have to do.

202
00:12:57.200 --> 00:12:58.640
Everyone. get back!

203
00:12:58.720 --> 00:13:00.880
Cédric. pull back and intervene later.

204
00:13:01.720 --> 00:13:03.680
Copy. Pulling back now.

205
00:13:04.520 --> 00:13:05.960
[engines decelerate]

206
00:13:07.480 --> 00:13:10.240
We need to get around! Left side. go!

207
00:13:10.320 --> 00:13:13.200
[suspenseful music continues]

208
00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:17.120
[children chattering indistinctly]

209
00:13:19.640 --> 00:13:21.000
Truck's almost at the school.

210
00:13:21.080 --> 00:13:24.200
[suspenseful music continues]

211
00:13:27.480 --> 00:13:29.160
[David] <i>We've got</i>
<i>a school bus on approach.</i>

212
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:36.160
<i>They'll cross paths in 900 yards.</i>

213
00:13:39.600 --> 00:13:43.520
[indistinct chatter]

214
00:13:50.280 --> 00:13:52.560
[David] <i>No one in the passenger seat.</i>
<i>Just the driver.</i>

215
00:14:00.640 --> 00:14:02.560
[indistinct chatter]

216
00:14:08.880 --> 00:14:10.880
[suspenseful music continues]

217
00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:17.480
[indistinct chatter]

218
00:14:21.560 --> 00:14:22.960
- [gunshot]
- [tires screeching]

219
00:14:23.960 --> 00:14:26.120
[children scream]

220
00:14:29.960 --> 00:14:32.080
[David] <i>Target immobilized.</i>

221
00:14:34.800 --> 00:14:36.280
- [children screaming]
- [driver] Shit!

222
00:14:39.080 --> 00:14:40.640
Alright. put me down here!

223
00:14:40.720 --> 00:14:42.720
David. I'm the negotiator.

224
00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:44.480
You get the kids off the bus.

225
00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:04.600
[driver] The bus is stuck.
I can't do anything. I'm locked down.

226
00:15:04.680 --> 00:15:06.200
They're coming down on a rope!

227
00:15:06.280 --> 00:15:08.400
[suspenseful music continues]

228
00:15:28.120 --> 00:15:30.080
[David] Police! Hands up. now!

229
00:15:30.160 --> 00:15:31.400
[breathing heavily]

230
00:15:31.480 --> 00:15:33.120
[David] Let me see your hands!

231
00:15:34.040 --> 00:15:36.200
[breathing heavily]

232
00:15:36.280 --> 00:15:38.160
He's crazy. There's more. look!

233
00:15:42.720 --> 00:15:44.880
[David] Both hands
above your head. right now!

234
00:15:46.680 --> 00:15:48.400
[breathing heavily]

235
00:15:48.480 --> 00:15:51.040
Raise both hands above your head!

236
00:15:52.520 --> 00:15:53.960
<i>Hands! Hands!</i>

237
00:15:54.040 --> 00:15:56.440
[driver] <i>I'm unarmed! They forced me!</i>

238
00:15:56.520 --> 00:15:58.720
I had no choice! [breathing heavily]

239
00:16:04.360 --> 00:16:06.920
[breathing heavily] They made me do it.
you have to believe me!

240
00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:09.520
They said if I get arrested.
I have to release the trigger!

241
00:16:09.600 --> 00:16:11.200
It's too late!

242
00:16:11.280 --> 00:16:15.280
[David] Hands above your head. right now!
I wanna see your hands. Show me!

243
00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:17.640
[operator] <i>Alpha Team in position.</i>

244
00:16:17.720 --> 00:16:20.080
- [children chattering indistinctly]
- [Cédric] Open up!

245
00:16:20.160 --> 00:16:24.480
Good afternoon. kids. Everything's okay.
We have to get off the bus now.

246
00:16:24.560 --> 00:16:27.520
My wife and kids… they're still at home!

247
00:16:27.600 --> 00:16:30.280
They said they'd kill me
if I didn't deliver the shipment.

248
00:16:30.360 --> 00:16:31.840
Hands! Hands above your head. now!

249
00:16:31.920 --> 00:16:35.320
[man on comm] <i>Evacuating the bus now.</i>
<i>Second team on approach.</i>

250
00:16:35.400 --> 00:16:36.360
[David] Both hands!

251
00:16:36.440 --> 00:16:37.640
<i>Your other hand too!</i>

252
00:16:37.720 --> 00:16:39.120
[Osman] <i>My name is Sergeant Osman.</i>

253
00:16:39.200 --> 00:16:40.640
[Chloé] I'm on it.

254
00:16:42.320 --> 00:16:45.080
- Let's all head out. one at a time!
- [officer 1] Stay nice and calm.

255
00:16:45.160 --> 00:16:46.960
[Cédric] Ma'am. can you take
a few of the kids?

256
00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:47.880
[officer 2] Let's go!

257
00:16:47.960 --> 00:16:50.400
[Osman] It's me or my family.
I have no choice!

258
00:16:50.480 --> 00:16:53.880
[David] Raise your left hand. slowly.
I need to see what you have in it!

259
00:16:53.960 --> 00:16:55.960
[officer speaking indistinctly over comm]

260
00:16:56.040 --> 00:16:58.040
[Osman breathing shakily]

261
00:17:01.480 --> 00:17:02.400
[Djibril] Fuck.

262
00:17:03.320 --> 00:17:05.120
[David] He has a release trigger.

263
00:17:05.200 --> 00:17:06.760
Please! Keep moving.

264
00:17:06.840 --> 00:17:08.880
Cédric. pick it up.
It could blow any second.

265
00:17:08.960 --> 00:17:11.280
- [officer 1] Step down and head that way.
- [officer 2] Move!

266
00:17:11.360 --> 00:17:12.960
[Christophe] <i>Tanya. what do we got?</i>

267
00:17:13.040 --> 00:17:15.480
[Tanya] Two crates. I'll inspect the door.

268
00:17:15.560 --> 00:17:18.360
[Chloé] <i>David. Osman is one of</i>
<i>two soldiers taken from the base.</i>

269
00:17:18.960 --> 00:17:20.680
- [David] Copy.
- [Chloé] <i>He may be a hostage.</i>

270
00:17:20.760 --> 00:17:23.440
- Okay. Sergeant Osman. right?
- Right.

271
00:17:23.520 --> 00:17:24.960
Okay.

272
00:17:25.040 --> 00:17:26.880
We're okay. Osman.

273
00:17:26.960 --> 00:17:29.360
Everything's fine.
Go help with the kids. please.

274
00:17:29.440 --> 00:17:30.480
Osman. look at me.

275
00:17:31.320 --> 00:17:33.840
- I'm putting my weapon away.
- Alright.

276
00:17:34.640 --> 00:17:36.640
[tense music playing]

277
00:17:40.200 --> 00:17:42.240
- [Cédric] Come on. keep moving!
- [officer 1] Good. go!

278
00:17:42.320 --> 00:17:44.280
- [officer 3] Let's go!
- [officer 4] Run! Go!

279
00:17:44.360 --> 00:17:46.080
- [kid] Are they gonna shoot?
- [officer 3] Go!

280
00:17:46.160 --> 00:17:47.320
[officer 2] Head that way!

281
00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:49.320
[Tanya] <i>Door check okay.</i>

282
00:17:49.400 --> 00:17:50.880
I'm opening it.

283
00:17:55.080 --> 00:17:55.920
<i>I'm going up.</i>

284
00:17:58.240 --> 00:17:59.880
[David] Look at me. Hey!

285
00:17:59.960 --> 00:18:01.320
You're okay.

286
00:18:01.960 --> 00:18:05.040
Keep looking at me.
Stay with me. Sergeant. Here. okay?

287
00:18:05.120 --> 00:18:08.000
I'm gonna walk slowly to the door
and open it so we can talk.

288
00:18:08.080 --> 00:18:09.840
- Is that alright?
- [Osman breathing heavily]

289
00:18:09.920 --> 00:18:11.360
Okay. I'm opening the door.

290
00:18:11.440 --> 00:18:12.400
Look at me.

291
00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:13.800
Hey. I'm here.

292
00:18:13.880 --> 00:18:15.080
Hey. here.

293
00:18:15.800 --> 00:18:18.000
Look at me. You have kids?

294
00:18:18.080 --> 00:18:20.080
Sarah and Nora. Yeah.

295
00:18:20.160 --> 00:18:22.240
Sarah and Nora. Beautiful names.

296
00:18:22.320 --> 00:18:24.440
- I think they're at my place--
- [David] I know they are.

297
00:18:24.520 --> 00:18:26.600
We're on our way to your family right now.

298
00:18:26.680 --> 00:18:28.720
We're helping you.
we're gonna help them too.

299
00:18:30.240 --> 00:18:32.320
[Cédric] Bus evacuated. The kids are safe.

300
00:18:32.400 --> 00:18:34.560
[tense music continues]

301
00:18:34.640 --> 00:18:38.160
[Tanya] No parallel circuit.
Everything's connected to the trigger.

302
00:18:38.240 --> 00:18:40.400
[breathing heavily]

303
00:18:40.480 --> 00:18:41.920
Look at me.

304
00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:44.640
Good. Now. I want you to think
of your daughters. Sarah and Nora.

305
00:18:44.720 --> 00:18:47.480
The more you think. the tighter
you're gonna squeeze your left hand.

306
00:18:48.080 --> 00:18:49.320
Alright.

307
00:18:49.400 --> 00:18:51.040
- [David] Okay? Keep squeezing.
- Okay.

308
00:18:51.120 --> 00:18:53.120
- [David] Squeeze your left hand. tight.
- Yeah.

309
00:18:53.720 --> 00:18:57.680
[Tanya] David. I need the trigger
to disarm the system.

310
00:18:58.200 --> 00:19:00.920
<i>We've got about</i>
<i>60 CL-20 tubes connected here.</i>

311
00:19:03.680 --> 00:19:06.800
Your right hand. you can lower it now.

312
00:19:06.880 --> 00:19:08.000
Okay. good. Very good.

313
00:19:08.600 --> 00:19:10.160
You're doing great. Look at me.

314
00:19:10.240 --> 00:19:12.240
[tense music continues]

315
00:19:12.320 --> 00:19:14.240
Extend your left hand towards me.

316
00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:18.040
Easy. easy.
Just hold out your left hand. Osman.

317
00:19:18.120 --> 00:19:22.720
[Tanya] I can't do anything with this.
I need the detonator.

318
00:19:23.240 --> 00:19:24.640
[tense music builds]

319
00:19:24.720 --> 00:19:26.880
Osman. look at me.
Think of your daughters.

320
00:19:26.960 --> 00:19:29.480
You're doing great. Right. just like that.

321
00:19:31.080 --> 00:19:32.640
<i>Great job. You're doing great.</i>

322
00:19:32.720 --> 00:19:34.520
Keep looking at me.

323
00:19:36.600 --> 00:19:37.920
Fantastic. Got it.

324
00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:39.600
[exhaling]

325
00:19:39.680 --> 00:19:40.840
[David] You're okay.

326
00:19:41.800 --> 00:19:43.360
- [Osman groans]
- [David] You're okay.

327
00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:46.240
Look. we can get you out of this now.

328
00:19:46.920 --> 00:19:48.600
It's almost over.

329
00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:51.400
[ominous music playing]

330
00:19:51.480 --> 00:19:53.840
Really great job. Well done. Sergeant.

331
00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:03.800
Okay. so. we found
Osman's family at home. unharmed.

332
00:20:03.880 --> 00:20:07.800
Gagged and bound. though.
The hostage takers had just left them.

333
00:20:07.880 --> 00:20:10.600
The sergeant couldn't have known.
so he kept following their orders.

334
00:20:10.680 --> 00:20:11.600
He told us his mission

335
00:20:11.680 --> 00:20:14.800
was to drop off his cargo
in an abandoned car park near Chartres.

336
00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:17.440
And if he was caught.
he was supposed to blow himself up.

337
00:20:17.520 --> 00:20:19.000
We didn't let him.

338
00:20:19.480 --> 00:20:20.440
Then at the rendezvous.

339
00:20:20.520 --> 00:20:24.040
we found a second refrigerated truck that
we hadn't known was taken from the base.

340
00:20:24.120 --> 00:20:27.640
Inside was the driver.
The second soldier who was taken hostage.

341
00:20:27.720 --> 00:20:31.280
They shot him. He must've had
the exact same orders as Osman.

342
00:20:31.360 --> 00:20:33.440
They threatened to kill his family
if he didn't obey.

343
00:20:33.520 --> 00:20:35.920
But they killed him
when he delivered the shipment.

344
00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:38.360
We didn't find anything in the truck.

345
00:20:38.440 --> 00:20:41.320
But we know he'd been transporting CL-20.

346
00:20:41.400 --> 00:20:43.320
The device they used was sophisticated.

347
00:20:43.400 --> 00:20:44.800
Almost professional grade.

348
00:20:44.880 --> 00:20:47.600
So it's not a stretch to say
this was well organized and planned.

349
00:20:48.480 --> 00:20:50.480
Tanya? All yours.

350
00:20:50.560 --> 00:20:52.240
[pensive music playing]

351
00:20:52.320 --> 00:20:55.360
CL-20. New explosive material.
State of the art.

352
00:20:55.440 --> 00:20:58.120
Originally a failed pesticide
from the States.

353
00:20:58.200 --> 00:21:00.240
- Can you start the video. please?
- Yeah.

354
00:21:01.840 --> 00:21:03.000
[Tanya] The FPA test base.

355
00:21:03.080 --> 00:21:05.760
The video is from the live fire test
five years ago.

356
00:21:07.000 --> 00:21:08.600
And that was only five pounds.

357
00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:11.600
It's the most powerful
conventional explosive to date.

358
00:21:11.680 --> 00:21:14.200
And handling it is extremely complex.

359
00:21:14.280 --> 00:21:16.360
Fewer than ten of us
have the right training.

360
00:21:16.440 --> 00:21:19.440
The last time I saw this stuff
was in Afghanistan. U.S. stockpile.

361
00:21:20.040 --> 00:21:22.920
Now. France has never
publicly admitted to having any.

362
00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:25.320
but of course.
that's what was stolen last night

363
00:21:25.400 --> 00:21:28.000
A ton. And only half of it
was in the truck we stopped.

364
00:21:28.080 --> 00:21:30.720
So there's still half a ton
of CL-20 out there?

365
00:21:30.800 --> 00:21:31.640
[Tanya] Yeah.

366
00:21:31.720 --> 00:21:34.200
Internal Security
and the Versailles police are on the case.

367
00:21:34.280 --> 00:21:35.840
I've put Recon at their disposal too.

368
00:21:35.920 --> 00:21:38.960
Christophe. you're briefing the team.
I want them ready as soon as we can.

369
00:21:39.040 --> 00:21:41.560
Of course. General. I'll take care of it.

370
00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:43.400
Well. let's get it done. Right.

371
00:21:43.480 --> 00:21:45.040
- Wanna eat?
- Yeah.

372
00:21:45.120 --> 00:21:46.520
[man] Right. let's go.

373
00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:50.600
[David] Hell of a stunt they pulled off.

374
00:21:50.680 --> 00:21:52.200
Hitting the warehouse…

375
00:21:53.120 --> 00:21:54.120
They've got balls.

376
00:21:54.200 --> 00:21:57.840
I'm not leaving you with an easy file
once I officially announce my departure.

377
00:21:57.920 --> 00:21:59.760
Hey. Houston. anyone home?

378
00:22:00.600 --> 00:22:02.360
How long's it been since we last spoke?

379
00:22:03.160 --> 00:22:05.640
- We're speaking now.
- Nah. I mean. really spoke.

380
00:22:06.440 --> 00:22:09.520
Well. yesterday you showed me that bike
you wanted to buy. I'm still in shock.

381
00:22:09.600 --> 00:22:10.440
David.

382
00:22:12.200 --> 00:22:13.440
What's going on?

383
00:22:13.520 --> 00:22:17.000
{\an8}Stage 3 pancreatic cancer.
That's what's going on.

384
00:22:17.760 --> 00:22:22.480
The doctor gave me five to six months.
But I'm stubborn. so more like seven.

385
00:22:23.400 --> 00:22:24.600
[sighs] But I'm done.

386
00:22:24.680 --> 00:22:26.120
[poignant music playing]

387
00:22:26.200 --> 00:22:28.360
- You're "done"?
- Mm-hmm.

388
00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:32.000
What're you talking about. you're "done"?
That's all you've got to say to me?

389
00:22:32.080 --> 00:22:33.760
After everything. you're just giving up?

390
00:22:33.840 --> 00:22:35.640
Some fights don't come
with a training manual.

391
00:22:35.720 --> 00:22:38.600
There's nothing to be done.
We can't prep for this.

392
00:22:39.400 --> 00:22:41.960
I'm not gonna beat this one. It's over.

393
00:22:42.040 --> 00:22:43.880
So I'm standing down.

394
00:22:44.480 --> 00:22:46.080
I want to spend time with my family.

395
00:22:47.440 --> 00:22:49.240
We haven't always been there.

396
00:22:50.400 --> 00:22:52.320
- Yeah.
- David.

397
00:22:53.680 --> 00:22:55.800
Don't feel guilty about leaving.

398
00:22:55.880 --> 00:22:57.960
It's the right decision for you and Jess.

399
00:22:58.040 --> 00:23:00.040
- Yeah.
- She's been waiting for you for so long.

400
00:23:00.120 --> 00:23:02.520
You've already had your best missions.

401
00:23:02.600 --> 00:23:05.320
And don't you worry about Max. okay?

402
00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:08.560
I'll make sure he doesn't make the cut.
even if he passes selection.

403
00:23:08.640 --> 00:23:10.440
Don't worry. he won't.

404
00:23:19.080 --> 00:23:22.480
- You're bad at small talk. You know that?
- [chuckles]

405
00:23:22.560 --> 00:23:23.480
[glasses clink]

406
00:23:23.560 --> 00:23:26.560
[playing "Impromptu No. 2"
by Franz Schubert]

407
00:23:40.240 --> 00:23:41.800
[piano music fades]

408
00:23:41.880 --> 00:23:43.680
[poignant music playing]

409
00:24:10.520 --> 00:24:12.520
- [music fades]
- [siren wailing distantly]

410
00:24:16.280 --> 00:24:18.600
["What It Is" by Amber Mark
playing over speakers]

411
00:24:18.680 --> 00:24:20.360
<i>♪ So there goes my heart ♪</i>

412
00:24:20.440 --> 00:24:21.840
Knock-knock. anyone home?

413
00:24:21.920 --> 00:24:25.240
<i>♪ I fell apart ♪</i>

414
00:24:25.320 --> 00:24:29.200
- [laughs]
<i>- ♪ Trying to love ♪</i>

415
00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:31.600
[both moaning]

416
00:24:31.680 --> 00:24:33.480
<i>♪ Wanna be free… ♪</i>

417
00:24:33.560 --> 00:24:36.000
- Where's Manon?
- She's at the gym. don't worry.

418
00:24:36.080 --> 00:24:38.320
- [chuckles] Lucky me.
- Yeah.

419
00:24:38.400 --> 00:24:42.440
<i>- ♪Is it in the stars? ♪</i>
- [chuckles. moans]

420
00:24:43.840 --> 00:24:44.840
[sighs]

421
00:24:45.800 --> 00:24:47.280
Thanks.

422
00:24:52.200 --> 00:24:54.200
All that stuff with Christophe…

423
00:24:54.840 --> 00:24:55.840
I can't believe it.

424
00:24:56.600 --> 00:24:59.120
Is it giving you second thoughts
about resigning?

425
00:24:59.880 --> 00:25:02.200
[David] No. The opposite. actually.

426
00:25:02.280 --> 00:25:03.840
I've made up my mind.

427
00:25:04.680 --> 00:25:06.920
And pretty soon.
we can live out our dream.

428
00:25:08.320 --> 00:25:10.360
A trip around the world by sailboat.

429
00:25:10.440 --> 00:25:14.040
I'll officially announce it
at the grad ceremony. Do things properly.

430
00:25:14.840 --> 00:25:16.920
And Max? He's graduating soon.

431
00:25:17.000 --> 00:25:19.640
- You gonna leave him alone in the field?
- No. but…

432
00:25:22.040 --> 00:25:24.400
Max won't be graduating. that's for sure.

433
00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:28.480
He's not gonna make the team.

434
00:25:29.760 --> 00:25:30.800
So?

435
00:25:31.560 --> 00:25:33.760
What d'you think?
Ready for the trip of a lifetime?

436
00:25:33.840 --> 00:25:36.400
Shit. Mom. my class was actually
at 9:00 this morning.

437
00:25:36.480 --> 00:25:38.120
- Hey. Dad!
- Hey!

438
00:25:38.200 --> 00:25:40.400
- I didn't know you were here.
- Mm.

439
00:25:44.080 --> 00:25:46.600
- What?
- You guys are being weird.

440
00:25:46.680 --> 00:25:49.680
- No. you're being weird.
- Yeah. You should stop being so weird.

441
00:25:49.760 --> 00:25:52.320
- Yeah.
- Hmm. okay. sure. Okay.

442
00:25:52.400 --> 00:25:55.080
- Can you drive me to class. Mom?
- Sorry. I've gotta go to work.

443
00:25:55.160 --> 00:25:58.160
- It's gonna take like hours by metro.
- I can take you. get your helmet.

444
00:25:59.760 --> 00:26:00.760
You sure?

445
00:26:01.760 --> 00:26:04.400
Of course. I'm sure.
I can't bring my girl to her piano lesson?

446
00:26:04.480 --> 00:26:06.120
- Sounds good.
- Let's go. grab your helmet.

447
00:26:06.200 --> 00:26:07.840
- Let me get changed. Be right back.
- Okay.

448
00:26:07.920 --> 00:26:09.680
[Manon] This is a first.

449
00:26:16.600 --> 00:26:17.920
Love you.

450
00:26:19.520 --> 00:26:23.280
Okay. it's 8:42 and we can get
to the 17th arrondissement in six minutes.

451
00:26:23.360 --> 00:26:25.960
- The 17th what?
- I'm gonna be able to do this more often.

452
00:26:26.040 --> 00:26:29.160
Drive you to classes. or whatever.
We can spend more time together.

453
00:26:29.240 --> 00:26:32.360
If you're not embarrassed
to hang out with your old man. that is.

454
00:26:32.440 --> 00:26:34.360
- But…
- I want to spend more time with you.

455
00:26:34.440 --> 00:26:37.000
Yeah. same. Dad. but it's not in the 17th.

456
00:26:37.080 --> 00:26:40.200
I switched to a different academy.
In Saclay.

457
00:26:40.280 --> 00:26:41.760
- In Saclay?
- Yeah.

458
00:26:42.760 --> 00:26:44.840
- We're gonna make it. Hold on tight.
- [starts bike]

459
00:26:44.920 --> 00:26:47.320
We won't make it. Oh. shit…

460
00:26:50.360 --> 00:26:51.880
Not exactly Club Med!

461
00:26:51.960 --> 00:26:53.240
You guys aren't cold?

462
00:26:53.320 --> 00:26:54.720
[all] No!

463
00:26:54.800 --> 00:26:57.000
Come on. even I'm freezing my ass off!

464
00:26:57.080 --> 00:26:58.560
You! You're not cold?

465
00:26:58.640 --> 00:27:00.600
[recruit] Not gonna lie. sir.
it's cold out here.

466
00:27:00.680 --> 00:27:03.000
Why didn't you say something?
We're not animals!

467
00:27:03.080 --> 00:27:05.160
Don't worry.
we'll get you warmed up real fast.

468
00:27:05.240 --> 00:27:06.720
Electric heater…

469
00:27:07.520 --> 00:27:10.320
You said you were cold. right? Here.

470
00:27:10.400 --> 00:27:11.720
Above your head.

471
00:27:12.280 --> 00:27:13.680
- [grunts]
- It warms you up. right?

472
00:27:13.760 --> 00:27:14.640
It does. yes. sir.

473
00:27:14.720 --> 00:27:18.840
Go on. pass it down to your buddy.
I want to see big smiles. guys!

474
00:27:20.400 --> 00:27:23.440
And careful with that one. okay?
It's the General's.

475
00:27:24.320 --> 00:27:26.400
If it touches the ground.
we're in trouble.

476
00:27:26.480 --> 00:27:29.160
Three… two… one… let's go!

477
00:27:29.240 --> 00:27:30.800
[intense music playing]

478
00:27:30.880 --> 00:27:34.480
The GIGN isn't just a task force.
it's the cream of the crop!

479
00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:38.400
We're the best there is.
But being the best comes at a cost.

480
00:27:41.120 --> 00:27:42.440
<i>If I'm going into battle.</i>

481
00:27:42.520 --> 00:27:46.920
I need to know in my bones
that I can put my life in your hands.

482
00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:49.480
That I can trust my comrades-in-arms.

483
00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:52.320
[intense music continues]

484
00:27:53.960 --> 00:27:56.000
<i>And if you want to be a part of this team.</i>

485
00:27:56.080 --> 00:28:00.480
we need to be sure that we can trust you.

486
00:28:00.560 --> 00:28:03.640
[Valère] Let's add a little atmosphere.
Yup. it's a smoke bomb.

487
00:28:03.720 --> 00:28:06.600
Alright. let's pick it up. slowpokes!
Don't stop!

488
00:28:06.680 --> 00:28:09.480
- [trainees coughing]
- [Valère] Come on! Keep going!

489
00:28:10.240 --> 00:28:11.880
I know you're exhausted.

490
00:28:11.960 --> 00:28:14.440
So if you can't take it anymore.
put it down.

491
00:28:16.120 --> 00:28:17.240
It's okay.

492
00:28:17.840 --> 00:28:19.480
You can reapply next year.

493
00:28:21.080 --> 00:28:22.600
[David] We're at a 100 meters.

494
00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:25.480
Remember that at 100 meters.
one notch is equal to a centimeter.

495
00:28:26.080 --> 00:28:28.800
I want you to put five bullets
dead center.

496
00:28:29.400 --> 00:28:30.640
Good luck. gentlemen.

497
00:28:32.040 --> 00:28:33.560
[intense music continues]

498
00:28:39.360 --> 00:28:41.560
[Cédric] <i>Two weeks ago.</i>
<i>there were 100 of you.</i>

499
00:28:41.640 --> 00:28:44.160
How many of you are left now? 14?

500
00:28:44.240 --> 00:28:47.680
After tomorrow.
if you don't have what it takes.

501
00:28:47.760 --> 00:28:49.720
<i>then we're gonna show you the door.</i>

502
00:28:50.800 --> 00:28:52.280
We could send you all home.

503
00:28:52.360 --> 00:28:53.360
We could.

504
00:28:53.440 --> 00:28:54.640
[gunshots]

505
00:28:59.240 --> 00:29:03.600
[David] <i>However. those of you that manage</i>
<i>to survive the selection process</i>

506
00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:05.360
will have earned your spot.

507
00:29:06.400 --> 00:29:09.160
Hey. don't forget
you're barely getting paid for this!

508
00:29:09.240 --> 00:29:11.600
If you wanna give up. now's your chance.

509
00:29:12.200 --> 00:29:14.480
[grunting]

510
00:29:14.560 --> 00:29:16.080
{\an8}[gunshots]

511
00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:27.400
Dropping out yet?

512
00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:30.040
Oh. hell no. not a chance!

513
00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:34.520
Just one more push to go. ma'am.

514
00:29:34.600 --> 00:29:35.760
[gunshots]

515
00:29:35.840 --> 00:29:38.000
- [grunts]
- [Valère] Congratulations! It's a boy!

516
00:29:39.400 --> 00:29:44.600
And if you're lucky enough
to join my section. or Cédric's.

517
00:29:44.680 --> 00:29:48.400
then I promise
we'll lay down our lives for you too.

518
00:29:48.480 --> 00:29:49.640
That's if you make it.

519
00:29:49.720 --> 00:29:50.920
Arms up!

520
00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:53.080
[gunshots]

521
00:30:03.440 --> 00:30:05.440
[David] We're changing the last test.

522
00:30:06.240 --> 00:30:07.440
To bomb defusal.

523
00:30:08.040 --> 00:30:10.360
We shouldn't be changing things up
at the last minute.

524
00:30:10.440 --> 00:30:12.960
- Besides. demo isn't our job. not really.
- Wait. what do you mean?

525
00:30:13.040 --> 00:30:14.880
We had explosives to deal with
just yesterday.

526
00:30:15.760 --> 00:30:17.400
Demo's a part of it.

527
00:30:18.600 --> 00:30:20.840
We adapt. You gotta be ready.

528
00:30:22.200 --> 00:30:24.160
- Are you changing it because of Max?
- Yeah.

529
00:30:24.760 --> 00:30:27.640
Ah. don't be an asshole. David.
You know what he's been through.

530
00:30:27.720 --> 00:30:30.760
Imagine we're on a mission.
and we come across a bomb. What do we do?

531
00:30:30.840 --> 00:30:33.960
Oh. c'mon. you don't want to test him.
you want him to fail.

532
00:30:35.520 --> 00:30:37.040
You think he'll end up like his father.

533
00:30:37.120 --> 00:30:39.960
[somber music playing]

534
00:30:46.840 --> 00:30:48.000
[music fades]

535
00:30:48.080 --> 00:30:51.400
- Djibril. we're changing the last test.
- Stop what you're doing.

536
00:30:51.480 --> 00:30:53.880
- [grunts]
- [Djibril] <i>We're changing things up.</i>

537
00:30:54.920 --> 00:30:56.920
[plane passes overhead]

538
00:30:57.440 --> 00:30:58.640
[zipping]

539
00:31:06.600 --> 00:31:07.560
Look at me.

540
00:31:14.080 --> 00:31:14.920
[beeps]

541
00:31:19.640 --> 00:31:20.560
You got this.

542
00:31:26.560 --> 00:31:27.520
[comm beeps]

543
00:31:30.440 --> 00:31:33.200
[tense music playing]

544
00:31:57.480 --> 00:31:59.480
[over radio] <i>Tanya for Max. you hear me?</i>

545
00:32:01.520 --> 00:32:02.800
Loud and clear.

546
00:32:02.880 --> 00:32:05.640
Hold on a minute. Just breathe.

547
00:32:06.160 --> 00:32:07.360
[exhales slowly]

548
00:32:08.680 --> 00:32:11.040
<i>There you go. Now move up.</i>

549
00:32:12.440 --> 00:32:14.480
- And keep your eyes peeled.
- Hey.

550
00:32:18.560 --> 00:32:21.200
[tense music continues]

551
00:32:33.760 --> 00:32:37.200
[hardcore metal music
blaring from speaker]

552
00:32:39.280 --> 00:32:41.200
[high-pitched distorted growl]

553
00:32:53.120 --> 00:32:54.160
[Max] <i>There's a wire.</i>

554
00:33:05.040 --> 00:33:06.840
<i>It leads towards the stairs.</i>

555
00:33:07.520 --> 00:33:08.720
I'm following it…

556
00:33:11.960 --> 00:33:13.720
Leads to an electric panel.

557
00:33:15.360 --> 00:33:16.200
It's…

558
00:33:16.280 --> 00:33:18.280
- [beeping]
- [Max] <i>Shit. I triggered something.</i>

559
00:33:18.880 --> 00:33:20.920
Better hurry. You have one minute.

560
00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:22.960
[metal music continues]

561
00:33:43.960 --> 00:33:46.040
[Max] I can see
an improvised explosive device.

562
00:33:47.400 --> 00:33:49.840
<i>One tube. some wires.</i>
<i>Okay. I know which one to cut.</i>

563
00:33:51.520 --> 00:33:52.640
[metal music continues]

564
00:33:54.760 --> 00:33:57.200
[song volume increases]

565
00:34:02.240 --> 00:34:04.080
[distortion intensifies]

566
00:34:05.160 --> 00:34:08.040
[distorted music builds]

567
00:34:10.200 --> 00:34:12.560
[distorted music continues]

568
00:34:21.680 --> 00:34:25.840
- [song fades]
- [hopeful music playing]

569
00:34:26.360 --> 00:34:29.480
[panting] Disarmed.

570
00:34:30.360 --> 00:34:31.400
[sighs]

571
00:34:33.400 --> 00:34:34.720
[Max chuckles]

572
00:34:34.800 --> 00:34:35.800
[Max sighs]

573
00:34:42.680 --> 00:34:45.920
[cheering]

574
00:34:46.760 --> 00:34:48.960
- Woo!
- Bravo!

575
00:34:49.040 --> 00:34:51.640
Alright. alright.
let's make some noise. yeah?

576
00:34:51.720 --> 00:34:53.320
- Bravo!
- [cheering continues]

577
00:34:54.520 --> 00:34:55.520
- [PJ] She said yes!
- Yeah!

578
00:34:55.600 --> 00:34:58.160
I'm getting married. guys!
I'm getting married!

579
00:34:58.240 --> 00:35:00.040
- [cheering]
- Bravo!

580
00:35:00.120 --> 00:35:01.160
[woman] Congrats!

581
00:35:01.240 --> 00:35:03.160
[distant applause]

582
00:35:10.080 --> 00:35:11.200
[sighs]

583
00:35:17.560 --> 00:35:19.400
[lively chatter]

584
00:35:19.480 --> 00:35:22.800
- It'll be a beautiful ceremony.
- We're off to a good start.

585
00:35:22.880 --> 00:35:25.480
- Hello. General.
- Hi. Jess. See you later.

586
00:35:26.160 --> 00:35:27.440
How are you?

587
00:35:32.280 --> 00:35:34.040
- Thank you for the message.
- Mm-hm.

588
00:35:34.120 --> 00:35:35.000
[Christophe chuckles]

589
00:35:36.120 --> 00:35:37.800
- It's the big night. huh?
- Sure is.

590
00:35:38.280 --> 00:35:40.520
- You seen David?
- No. not yet.

591
00:35:49.960 --> 00:35:51.160
[sighs]

592
00:35:51.240 --> 00:35:53.240
[lively chatter continues distantly]

593
00:36:14.040 --> 00:36:15.680
It's been a long time.

594
00:36:15.760 --> 00:36:17.440
[Nathalie] Fifteen years.

595
00:36:17.520 --> 00:36:19.520
[somber music playing]

596
00:36:22.880 --> 00:36:26.520
- You promised he'd never make the Force.
- Oh. Nathalie…

597
00:36:27.480 --> 00:36:31.560
I tried everything.
I put up roadblocks everywhere I could.

598
00:36:32.320 --> 00:36:35.400
I was tougher on him than all the others.
I practically shoved him out the door.

599
00:36:36.440 --> 00:36:38.160
But what else was I supposed to do?

600
00:36:40.040 --> 00:36:41.200
He's brilliant.

601
00:36:47.120 --> 00:36:49.120
That doesn't stop someone
from getting killed.

602
00:36:52.920 --> 00:36:54.040
If I lose him too…

603
00:36:55.480 --> 00:36:59.480
This fucking place… already took Laurent.

604
00:37:01.760 --> 00:37:03.600
Now it's trying to take my boy?

605
00:37:05.760 --> 00:37:07.120
You have to promise me

606
00:37:07.880 --> 00:37:09.640
that you'll look out for him.

607
00:37:09.720 --> 00:37:12.200
That you'll never leave Max alone.

608
00:37:12.760 --> 00:37:13.840
Promise me.

609
00:37:14.920 --> 00:37:16.160
Never.

610
00:37:17.880 --> 00:37:18.800
Don't forget.

611
00:37:19.400 --> 00:37:23.600
if it hadn't been for you.
I never would've lost my husband.

612
00:37:29.200 --> 00:37:31.200
[somber music continues]

613
00:37:53.520 --> 00:37:54.720
[cheering]

614
00:37:54.800 --> 00:37:56.560
Pierre-Jean Lemoine.

615
00:37:56.640 --> 00:37:58.760
Tactical Unit. Section One.

616
00:37:58.840 --> 00:38:01.840
[dramatic music playing]

617
00:38:07.160 --> 00:38:08.640
Wear it with dignity and pride.

618
00:38:09.480 --> 00:38:11.320
[applause]

619
00:38:11.400 --> 00:38:14.400
[cheering and whistling]

620
00:38:14.480 --> 00:38:16.000
NATIONAL GENDARMERIE
INTERVENTION GROUP

621
00:38:21.760 --> 00:38:23.240
[general] Raphaëlle Ricci.

622
00:38:23.320 --> 00:38:24.960
Reconnaissance and Intelligence.

623
00:38:25.040 --> 00:38:27.040
[dramatic music continues]

624
00:38:35.120 --> 00:38:37.120
Wear it with dignity and pride.

625
00:38:37.640 --> 00:38:39.320
[applause]

626
00:38:39.400 --> 00:38:42.360
[cheering and whistling]

627
00:38:42.960 --> 00:38:44.080
Bravo!

628
00:38:52.760 --> 00:38:56.360
[general] Maxime Villiers.
Tactical Unit. Section One.

629
00:38:59.560 --> 00:39:01.600
[dramatic music continues]

630
00:39:21.560 --> 00:39:23.360
Wear it with dignity and pride.

631
00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:27.240
- [cheering and whistling]
- [man] Alright!

632
00:39:38.920 --> 00:39:41.400
You wanted to say a few words. didn't you?

633
00:39:44.360 --> 00:39:46.440
[music turns pensive]

634
00:39:50.920 --> 00:39:52.320
I'm sorry. I'm not very. uh…

635
00:39:53.720 --> 00:39:55.520
good at all this stuff.

636
00:39:58.440 --> 00:40:00.200
Today is special.

637
00:40:00.280 --> 00:40:02.880
You've all worked hard.
Today marks a turning point.

638
00:40:03.680 --> 00:40:05.560
For you as well as for me.

639
00:40:06.640 --> 00:40:10.040
You endured a rigorous
and ruthless selection process

640
00:40:10.120 --> 00:40:12.280
and now you're officially
part of the team.

641
00:40:14.560 --> 00:40:15.560
Well done.

642
00:40:16.160 --> 00:40:17.880
This team is exceptional.

643
00:40:17.960 --> 00:40:20.240
You're going to work and live
side by side.

644
00:40:21.040 --> 00:40:22.720
It's kind of like a family.

645
00:40:22.800 --> 00:40:24.560
One that demands a lot of you.

646
00:40:27.080 --> 00:40:28.800
We'll need to make sacrifices.

647
00:40:29.840 --> 00:40:34.200
And I believe that these sacrifices
cannot be made alone.

648
00:40:35.120 --> 00:40:38.520
Your families. their support and love.
make this job possible.

649
00:40:40.200 --> 00:40:42.200
But this wasn't their idea.

650
00:40:43.160 --> 00:40:45.560
It wasn't by choice.
They've been forced into it.

651
00:40:46.720 --> 00:40:48.160
So. thank you.

652
00:40:49.480 --> 00:40:50.960
Thanks. because you…

653
00:40:51.960 --> 00:40:53.960
show us what true courage looks like.

654
00:40:54.560 --> 00:40:56.560
You're probably braver than any of us.

655
00:40:58.120 --> 00:40:59.560
We ask you to do the impossible.

656
00:41:00.160 --> 00:41:04.680
To put up with delays.
with late nights. with beeping pagers.

657
00:41:04.760 --> 00:41:07.600
With the fear you must feel
when we're sent on a mission.

658
00:41:08.800 --> 00:41:12.360
Especially the tough ones.
Sometimes. far away.

659
00:41:12.440 --> 00:41:14.760
So who are the real heroes?

660
00:41:15.480 --> 00:41:16.640
Maybe it's your families.

661
00:41:18.520 --> 00:41:20.840
- Alright. let's celebrate!
- [applause]

662
00:41:20.920 --> 00:41:23.000
See you tomorrow in the field.

663
00:41:23.080 --> 00:41:24.560
[cheering and whistling]

664
00:41:24.640 --> 00:41:27.040
[music turns dramatic]

665
00:41:28.000 --> 00:41:29.120
Bravo!

666
00:41:29.800 --> 00:41:30.880
[whistling]

667
00:41:37.480 --> 00:41:38.920
[sighs]

668
00:41:52.000 --> 00:41:53.920
[electronic dance music
playing over speakers]

669
00:41:54.000 --> 00:41:56.000
[lively chatter]

670
00:42:19.280 --> 00:42:21.360
I just want to thank you for your support.

671
00:42:21.440 --> 00:42:24.240
- It's my pleasure. You earned your spot.
- Thanks.

672
00:42:28.440 --> 00:42:31.080
[man] Hey. David!
Where're you going? Come back!

673
00:42:55.840 --> 00:42:57.440
I can't abandon Max.

674
00:43:00.040 --> 00:43:01.160
I just can't.

675
00:43:01.240 --> 00:43:03.240
[poignant music playing]

676
00:43:08.440 --> 00:43:10.680
They offered me a promotion at the bank.

677
00:43:12.480 --> 00:43:15.400
It's a… it's a huge opportunity.

678
00:43:17.440 --> 00:43:18.760
That's amazing.

679
00:43:21.640 --> 00:43:23.240
It's in Singapore.

680
00:43:26.400 --> 00:43:28.560
I didn't mention it because it just…

681
00:43:29.280 --> 00:43:30.920
It was out of the question.

682
00:43:32.000 --> 00:43:34.760
I know you wouldn't want
to move there with me. and…

683
00:43:37.240 --> 00:43:38.960
I couldn't break up our family.

684
00:43:39.040 --> 00:43:40.880
Nothing's more important to me.

685
00:43:44.600 --> 00:43:46.720
But obviously. it's different for you.

686
00:43:49.280 --> 00:43:51.200
Me and Manon have never come first.

687
00:43:51.280 --> 00:43:52.360
That's not…

688
00:43:52.440 --> 00:43:55.000
But you have… Jess.

689
00:43:57.080 --> 00:43:58.080
And Max?

690
00:43:59.920 --> 00:44:02.200
Are you gonna tell him
why you're doing this?

691
00:44:06.760 --> 00:44:07.920
[David sighs]

692
00:44:09.040 --> 00:44:11.640
Just… give me a bit more time. please.

693
00:44:16.160 --> 00:44:18.880
As for Singapore. I'm gonna take it.

694
00:44:26.360 --> 00:44:27.840
I'm going back to Paris.

695
00:44:38.920 --> 00:44:40.640
[both laugh]

696
00:44:45.400 --> 00:44:47.160
Why'd you ask for the tactical team?

697
00:44:47.240 --> 00:44:50.360
Okay. 'cause they're the best
and all that. but. uh…

698
00:44:51.040 --> 00:44:53.280
What's. like. the real reason?

699
00:44:53.960 --> 00:44:56.600
You know David and my dad
were in the same section here?

700
00:44:57.120 --> 00:44:58.960
They were like brothers.

701
00:45:00.120 --> 00:45:02.320
One day.
something went wrong on a mission.

702
00:45:02.400 --> 00:45:03.760
[poignant music playing]

703
00:45:03.840 --> 00:45:05.040
The explosion?

704
00:45:05.640 --> 00:45:06.600
Yeah.

705
00:45:06.680 --> 00:45:08.400
Fifteen years ago. After Dad died.

706
00:45:08.480 --> 00:45:11.600
Mom wanted to get me
as far away from them as she could.

707
00:45:12.440 --> 00:45:13.480
I only came back this year.

708
00:45:14.440 --> 00:45:15.280
Mm.

709
00:45:16.080 --> 00:45:19.520
But my home. my real home.
it's always been here.

710
00:45:20.640 --> 00:45:22.000
In Satory.

711
00:45:22.760 --> 00:45:24.120
Right here. like my dad.

712
00:45:25.600 --> 00:45:26.920
- [inhales]
- [Rapha] Hm.

713
00:45:31.240 --> 00:45:32.760
What about you?

714
00:45:32.840 --> 00:45:35.360
Intel and Recon. that's…
that's what you wanted?

715
00:45:36.760 --> 00:45:39.880
- Don't think I can't hear that tone.
- [chuckles]

716
00:45:40.760 --> 00:45:41.720
To be honest. uh…

717
00:45:42.320 --> 00:45:46.520
Recon has… always been my dream.
It's what I'm meant to do.

718
00:45:47.280 --> 00:45:48.760
And I'm really good at it.

719
00:45:49.680 --> 00:45:51.840
Tracking criminals. following leads…

720
00:45:55.680 --> 00:45:57.680
[Christophe] I don't get
what you're doing. David.

721
00:45:59.520 --> 00:46:02.400
At least move Max to another section.
Come on! Use your head!

722
00:46:04.480 --> 00:46:05.800
I've forgiven you.

723
00:46:05.880 --> 00:46:08.320
But him? Does he even know
what really happened?

724
00:46:09.360 --> 00:46:10.280
No.

725
00:46:10.360 --> 00:46:12.760
[tense music playing]

726
00:46:14.880 --> 00:46:16.400
[dramatic sting plays]

727
00:46:19.560 --> 00:46:21.920
[tense music continues]

728
00:46:25.760 --> 00:46:29.560
How are you planning on keeping
an eye on him in the field? Huh?

729
00:46:29.640 --> 00:46:30.640
What's your plan?

730
00:46:37.600 --> 00:46:39.840
I know you think you're staying for him.
but you're not.

731
00:46:49.120 --> 00:46:51.000
You're kidding yourself. my friend.

732
00:46:58.040 --> 00:46:59.640
[tense music builds]

733
00:47:10.400 --> 00:47:12.600
[dramatic music playing]

734
00:48:24.040 --> 00:48:26.040
[intense music playing]

735
00:49:57.040 --> 00:49:59.040
[dramatic music playing]

736
00:50:00.305 --> 00:51:00.566
